JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries will brief the media on the outbreak of bird flu in the country.Minister Senzeni Zokwana will highlight the government's plan of action.Earlier this week, a second case of bird flu was confirmed on a farm in Mpumalanga.WATCH: What is bird flu and can you get it?About 25,000 birds will be culled after the virus was detected in Standerton.Several neighbouring countries have banned poultry imports from South Africa.The department has ordered a ban on the sale of live chickens.Poultry producers are worried about the effects of the bird flu on the local industry.eNCA